-- EBay CFO sees profit per share up 15 to 19 percent a year over next 3 years
-- 
-- Thu Mar 28, 2013 4:25pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/28/us-ebay-earnings-idUSBRE92R0X220130328

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - EBay Inc Chief Financial Officer Bob Swan forecast earnings per share growth of 15 percent to 19 percent a year over the next three years 
 Swan also said PayPal's new offline business can generate transaction margins of about 40 percent. He also forecast cash flow of more than $11 billion over the next three years. (Reporting by  Alistair Barr )